  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a \u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb5 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Association of Government Medical Officers to make wearing of face masks mandatory",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The new outbreak of Covid-19 is on the rise again. Therefore, the decision taken earlier by the Ministry of Health regarding the wearing of masks should be reconsidered, said Director of the Government Medical Officers' Association, Dr. Haritha Alutke.",
        "He said this in reference to the resurgence of the Covid-19 virus in a new form.",
        "The new outbreak of Covid-19 is on the rise again. Therefore, the decision taken earlier by the Ministry of Health regarding wearing face mask should be reconsidered. Authorities should focus on making face coverings mandatory at least for Covid high alert zones.",
        "While many countries in the world are taking formal decisions regarding Covid-19, Sri Lanka has not been paying attention to this issue so far. Also, the currently defunct Covid-related technical committee should be reconvened and steps should be taken to prevent future disasters.",
        "The new corona virus called B.A.5 has spread all over the world and the number of patients has increased by 30 percent. So far no program has been carried out to find out whether this new type of epidemic, which is spreading very quickly, has arrived in Sri Lanka. A program should be started to inform people that there may be new corona patients among the viral fever patients who are spreading these days.",
        "In addition, the lack of resources, medicine and intensive care unit facilities that occurred in the past are still lacking in the hospital structures. So there is a cautious situation in the next two months. Presently B.C.R. And if 1,000 antigen tests are performed, 50 patients will be identified. Similarly, a patient dies once every 3 days."
      ],
